post_text: This is a message from Winside Public School about the start of the 20 – 21 school year. I am excited to announce that our buildings will be open to our students starting August 13th at 8:00 A.M. We will be sending out more detailed information in the coming weeks about our reopening plan. I did want to outline that we have three levels to our plan (Green, Yellow, Red). We will be starting in Green at this time. Masks are optional but encouraged in this level, as we can social distance. There are several areas that masks may be required (bus and vans) in Green. If this is the case the district will provide several cloth reusable masks to students and staff. If we move into the Yellow, masks will be required. This is a consistently changing pandemic and all mask requirements or color levels could change before school starts. If that happens, we will let you know immediately. Also, if you choose to send your student to school in a mask please make sure it is appropriate for school.

Happy FCCLA week everyone! FCCLA is a great organization that teaches students to build real world skills through competitive events and engaging youth leaders from across the nation. Each day this week we will be celebrating something different in order to shine light on different aspects that FCCLA focuses on. Today is "What's Your FCCLA Story?" Day.

This is our very first year here at Winside, but our numbers are very strong! Below you can see all the happy faces of our FCCLA chapter (minus a few). We have so many ideas and goals that we want to accomplish in the next year. We are super excited to see where we can take our chapter! Be on the lookout for more posts this week of what we are doing to celebrate FCCLA week!

New in school- FCCLA has made it way to Winside! FCCLA is a career and technical student lead organization that functions as a part of the Family and Consumer Sciences education curriculum that provides opportunities for active student participation at local, state, and national levels. Winside’s chapter is booming with 24 student members!!
Through an application process, the advisor Mrs. Heikes chose the officers for this and next year’s FCCLA chapter. We are so proud to announce the chosen officers’ names listed below:
President: Kylie Cautrell
Vice President: Hope Cummins
District Representative: Jackie Escalante
Secretary: Caden Reed
Treasurer: Julissa Redwing
National Programs: Camrynn Marx
Public Relations: Dax Behmer
Membership: Dean Kruger
Congrats officers!!
